<li id="cite_note-Laffter_at_Heritage-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Laffter_at_Heritage_24-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a href="Arthur_Laffer" title="Arthur Laffer">Arthur Laffer</a> (June 1, 2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.heritage.org/Research/Taxes/bg1765.cfm">"The Laffer Cruve, Past, Present and Future"</a>. Heritage Foundation<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.heritage.org/Research/Taxes/bg1765.cfm">http://www.heritage.org/Research/Taxes/bg1765.cfm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2007-12-11</span>.</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal" id="CITEREFGates1967">Gates, Warren E. (1967). "The Spread of Ibn Khaldûn's Ideas on Climate and Culture". <i>Journal of the History of Ideas</i> (University of Pennsylvania Press) <b>28</b> (3): 415–422. <a href="Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307/2708627">10.2307/2708627</a>.</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal" id="CITEREFDhaouadi1990">Dhaouadi, M. (1 September 1990). "IBN KHALDUN: THE FOUNDING FATHER OF EASTERN SOCIOLOGY". <i>International Sociology</i> <b>5</b> (3): 319–335. <a href="Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1177/026858090005003007">10.1177/026858090005003007</a>.</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal" id="CITEREFHaddad1977">Haddad, L. (1 May 1977). "A FOURTEENTH-CENTURY THEORY OF ECONOMIC GROWTH AND DEVELOPMENT". <i>Kyklos</i> <b>30</b> (2): 195–213. <a href="Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-6435.1977.tb02006.x">10.1111/j.1467-6435.1977.tb02006.x</a>.</span></span></li>
</ol>
